        <h1>Join The Globe Church's Week of Prayer</h1>
        <p>It has become our practice each year as we head into December to set aside a week on the calendar to call our church family to pray.</p>
        <p>Each year we have come together in the morning for breakfast, we have met in small groups and large gatherings when we could, individually on our own, setting time in our day to come before our God in praise and prayer.</p>
        <p>Throughout the week we'll be focusing on the theme of prayer showing our dependence on God. Jesus spent his mornings coming to God in prayer, the Lord's Prayer calls us to come and ask God for our daily bread. Prayer in it's essence is a display of dependance on our heavenly Father. Over <a href="https://www.globe.church/resources/delighting-in-dependence">on the blog</a> Yusuf has shared more about how this theme is so central to our week. <a href="https://www.globe.church/resources/delighting-in-dependence">Read it now</a>.</p> 
        <p>Will you commit to joining us this year? We pray it will be significant in developing our relationship with our Father.</p>
        <p><a href="#mc-embedded-subscribe-form" class="u-btn u-btn--dark u-btn--arrowed">Commit to pray now</a></p>

        <hr class="st-divider" />

        <h1>The Schedule</h1>

